sql:
SELECT team_id, COUNT(DISTINCT season_year) AS total_seasons_played
FROM team_records
GROUP BY team_id;

external_knowledge:
- A "successful team" refers to a team with a win percentage greater than 0.5, indicating they have won more than half of their games; 
- "Substantial minutes" is defined as 20 minutes played, indicating active participation by the player; 
- "Multiple games" means more than five recorded games to ensure a fair average.
